{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast to receptive skills, Scholes & Nancy (1985) view writing and speaking skills as productive skills that are both ways of thinking and a means of communication.",
    "In addition, Nunan (2003) asserts that writing is a mental process of inventing ideas, thinking about how to articulate them, and organizing them into statements, sentences, or paragraphs that are clear for the readers to comprehend.",
    "In this paper, the author supports the viewpoint that writing is a productive skill used to communicate people's thoughts, opinions, feelings, etc., in written forms.",
    "Academic writing refers to the type of writing used for academic purposes in colleges or universities.",
    "It is considered the principal means of communication between scholars, lecturers, and students in academic subjects and disciplines in higher education (Greene & Lidinsky, 2015; Johnson, 2016)."
  ]
}